author: Chris Pleasance For Daily Mail Australia
title: Single guy sets up website to find his 'lifelong partner' | Daily Mail Online
text: 'Please don't be shy': Single hipster DJ sets up a website to find a 'funny girl with a top personality' - but he's only had two offers Drew Kilpatrick, 29, from Sydney, says site was created as a joke by a housemate But he found it funny so he left it up and is in the market for a long-term partner He has received two replies, including one woman who sent him a questionnaire Says ideal partner is funny, with a 'top personality' and 'good looks don't hurt'
